# 📘 JavaScript Practice Questions (Objects + Arrays)

> A collection of 40 JavaScript problems focused on Objects and Arrays.
> Perfect for beginners to intermediate learners 💻

---

## 🔹 Basic Level (20 Questions)

### 1. Sum values in object arrays

**Input:**

```js
{ food: [10, 20, 30], travel: [5, 15], bills: [40, 60] }
```

**Output:**

```js
{ food: 60, travel: 20, bills: 100 }
```

---

### 2. Count word occurrences in array

**Input:**

```js
["apple", "banana", "apple", "orange", "banana", "apple"]
```

**Output:**

```js
{ apple: 3, banana: 2, orange: 1 }
```

---

### 3. Swap keys and values of object

**Input:**

```js
{ a: "x", b: "y", c: "z" }
```

**Output:**

```js
{ x: "a", y: "b", z: "c" }
```

---

### 4. Find the largest value key

**Input:**

```js
{ a: 10, b: 50, c: 20 }
```

**Output:**

```
b
```

---

### 5. Flatten object of arrays

**Input:**

```js
{ fruits: ["apple", "banana"], veggies: ["carrot", "pea"] }
```

**Output:**

```js
["apple", "banana", "carrot", "pea"]
```

---

### 6. Group people by city

**Input:**

```js
[
  { name: "A", city: "Delhi" },
  { name: "B", city: "Mumbai" },
  { name: "C", city: "Delhi" }
]
```

**Output:**

```js
{ Delhi: ["A", "C"], Mumbai: ["B"] }
```

---

### 7. Filter object by values > 50

```js
Input: { a: 20, b: 60, c: 40, d: 90 }
Output: { b: 60, d: 90 }
```

---

### 8. Find student with highest average marks

```js
Input: { A: [80, 90], B: [70, 75, 85] }
Output: A
```

---

### 9. Unique values across all object arrays

```js
Input: { x: [1,2,3], y: [2,3,4], z: [4,5] }
Output: [1,2,3,4,5]
```

---

### 10. Pick only given keys from object

```js
Input: { name: "Rahul", age: 23, city: "Noida" }, ["name","city"]
Output: { name: "Rahul", city: "Noida" }
```

---

### 11. Sort object entries by values (ascending)

```js
Input: { a: 3, b: 1, c: 2 }
Output: [["b",1], ["c",2], ["a",3]]
```

---

### 12. Count number of keys in object

```js
Input: { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }
Output: 3
```

---

### 13. Capitalize string values inside object

```js
Input: { name: "alice", city: "delhi" }
Output: { name: "Alice", city: "Delhi" }
```

---

### 14. Convert object to query string

```js
Input: { name: "Alice", age: 25 }
Output: "name=Alice&age=25"
```

---

### 15. Count even and odd numbers in array

```js
Input: [1,2,3,4,5,6]
Output: { even: 3, odd: 3 }
```

---

### 16. Find common keys between two objects

```js
Input: { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }, { b: 4, c: 5, d: 6 }
Output: ["b","c"]
```

---

### 17. Convert array of objects to lookup by id

```js
Input: [{ id: 1, name: "A" }, { id: 2, name: "B" }]
Output: { 1: { id:1, name:"A" }, 2: { id:2, name:"B" } }
```

---

### 18. Check if all values in object are numbers

```js
Input: { a: 1, b: "hello", c: 3 }
Output: false
```

---

## 🔹 Intermediate Level (20 Questions)

### 19. Sum all transactions per user

```js
Input:
[
  { user: "A", amount: 100 },
  { user: "B", amount: 200 },
  { user: "A", amount: 50 }
]

Output:
{ A: 150, B: 200 }
```

---

### 20. Transform API response to object (id → name)

```js
Input:
[
  { id: 1, name: "Alice" },
  { id: 2, name: "Bob" }
]

Output:
{ 1: "Alice", 2: "Bob" }
```

---

### 21. Remove falsy values from object

```js
Input: { a: 0, b: null, c: "hello", d: undefined, e: 5 }
Output: { c: "hello", e: 5 }
```

---

### 22. Check for permissions from roles

```js
roles = { admin:["read","write"], user:["read"], staff:["write"] }
checkRole = "user"
action = "write"

Output: false
```

---

### 23. Transform array of orders into revenue per category

```js
Input:
[
  { category: "electronics", price: 100 },
  { category: "clothes", price: 50 },
  { category: "electronics", price: 200 }
]

Output:
{ electronics: 300, clothes: 50 }
```

---

### 24. Remove duplicate objects by id

```js
Input:
[
  { id: 1, name: "A" },
  { id: 2, name: "B" },
  { id: 1, name: "A" }
]

Output:
[
  { id: 1, name: "A" },
  { id: 2, name: "B" }
]
```

---

### 25. Chunk object entries into groups of size

```js
Input: { a: 1, b: 2, c: 3, d: 4 }, size=2
Output: [ [["a",1],["b",2]], [["c",3],["d",4]] ]
```

---

### 26. Find longest string among object values

```js
Input: { a: "apple", b: "banana", c: "kiwi" }
Output: banana
```

---

### 27. Language translation transform (HARD)

```js
Input:
{
  en: { hello: "Hello", bye: "Goodbye" },
  fr: { hello: "Bonjour", bye: "Au revoir" },
  es: { hello: "Hola" }
}

Output:
{
  hello: { en: "Hello", fr: "Bonjour", es: "Hola" },
  bye: { en: "Goodbye", fr: "Au revoir" }
}
```

---

### 28. Build index of ids grouped by category

```js
Input:
[
  { id: 1, category: "fruit" },
  { id: 2, category: "veggie" },
  { id: 3, category: "fruit" }
]

Output:
{ fruit: [1,3], veggie: [2] }
```

---

### 29. Remove deeply nested key from object

```js
Input: { a: { b: { c: 1, d: 2 } } }, remove "c"
Output: { a: { b: { d: 2 } } }
```

---

### 30. Check if two objects are deeply equal

```js
Input: { a: { x: 1, y: 2 } }, { a: { x: 1, y: 2 } }
Output: true
```

---

### 31. Deep flatten nested arrays inside object

```js
Input: { a: [1, [2, [3]]], b: [4, [5]] }
Output: { a: [1,2,3], b: [4,5] }
```

---

### 32. Find most repeated word across categories

```js
Input: { fruits: ["apple","apple","banana"], drinks: ["apple","tea"] }
Output: apple
```

---

### 33. Find intersection of all arrays in object

```js
Input: { a: [1,2,3], b: [2,3,4], c: [3,4,5] }
Output: [3]
```

---

### 34. Deep merge two nested objects

```js
Input:
{ a: { x: 1, y: 2 } }
{ a: { y: 3, z: 4 } }

Output:
{ a: { x: 1, y: 3, z: 4 } }
```

---

### 35. Nested object destructuring

```js
Input: { user: { profile: { name: "Alice", age: 25 } } }
Output: Alice 25
```

---

### 36. Find top N keys by value

```js
Input: { a: 10, b: 50, c: 30, d: 40 }, N=2
Output: ["b","d"]
```

---

### 37. Sort array of objects by name then age

```js
Input:
[
  { name: "Alice", age: 30 },
  { name: "Bob", age: 25 },
  { name: "Alice", age: 22 }
]

Output:
[
  { name: "Alice", age: 22 },
  { name: "Alice", age: 30 },
  { name: "Bob", age: 25 }
]
```

---

### 38. Reconcile two lists (missing + extra items)

```js
Input:
expected:["a","b","c"]
actual:["b","c","d"]

Output:
{ missing:["a"], extra:["d"] }
```

---

### 39. Merge two objects (override second)

```js
Input:
{ a: 10, b: 20 }
{ a: 5, c: 15 }

Output:
{ a: 5, b: 20, c: 15 }
```

---

